bug.short_desc: [formatter] format save action fails with SIOOBE

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 185417 My Formatter Settings
I20101208-1300

Created attachment 185438 Proposed fix
This should work better.
Setting as major as this is causing the formatter to fail.

(In reply to comment #3) > Created an attachment (id=185438) [details] > Proposed fix > > This should work better.
Agreed, that looks good :-S...
Benno, a test case to reproduce this issue would help us to add a non-regression test :-)

I am not sure we should release this patch as long as we don't have a regression test. I put a breakpoint in this code running all the formatter tests and I only hit the breakpoint once with a replacement string length of 2. So clearly we miss test cases that are using that code intensively.
*** Bug 333552 has been marked as a duplicate of this bug. ***
Released for 3.7M5. A regression test is still needed for this issue.

(In reply to comment #8) > Released for 3.7M5. > A regression test is still needed for this issue.
Sorry, it's hard to find steps, because after the exception is thrown undo is broken for me, hence I can not go back to the state before the exception was thrown and reproduce the problem.

I found reproducible steps from which you can hopefully extract a test case. I also verified that the fix works.
Steps: 1. start new workspace 2. import the attached ZIP as 'Existing Projects into Workspace' 3. Enable Java > Editor > Save Actions - enable Format source code - choose Format edited lines 4. open type 'RecipeDocumentProvider' 5. expand the collapsed imports 6. on the third import (line 15) type "xxx" after "org.eclipse" 7. save ==> bug
Created attachment 186158 ZIP with test project

Verified for 3.7M5 using build I20110124-1800.
Opened bug 335309 to follow up on adding a regression test
